### 8. Error enhancement when no OAuth fallback exists

When the env token fallback fails (no stored OAuth) and the 401/403 propagates, the error message should explain the situation. In the API error handling path (where `ApiError` is constructed from HTTP responses):

If `getRawEnvToken()` is set and status is 401 or 403, throw `AuthError` instead of `ApiError`:
```
API returned 403. SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN is set but lacks permissions for this endpoint.
  Run 'sentry auth login' to authenticate with OAuth, or set SENTRY_IGNORE_ENV_TOKEN=1.
```

This converts the error from `ApiError` (which auto-login ignores) to `AuthError` (which triggers auto-login in interactive mode).

