## Testing

### Unit tests: `test/lib/db/env-token-cache.test.ts` (new)
- `isEndpointInsufficient` returns false when no entry exists
- `markEndpointInsufficient` + `isEndpointInsufficient` round-trip
- Same token, different endpoint → independent marks
- Different token, same endpoint → independent marks
- `clearEnvTokenCache` wipes all entries
- `clearEnvTokenCacheForToken` only wipes entries for that token
- Entries older than 24h TTL are ignored by `isEndpointInsufficient`
- Re-marking an endpoint refreshes its `created_at` (UPSERT behavior)

### Unit tests: `test/lib/db/auth.test.ts` (extend existing)
- `getEnvToken()` returns undefined when `SENTRY_IGNORE_ENV_TOKEN` is set
- `getRawEnvToken()` returns token even when `SENTRY_IGNORE_ENV_TOKEN` is set
- `hasStoredAuthToken()` returns true/false correctly
- `refreshToken({ skipEnv: true })` skips env token and uses OAuth

### Unit tests: `test/lib/sentry-client.test.ts` (extend or new)
- `fetchWithRetry` uses OAuth when endpoint is pre-marked insufficient
- `handleResponse` marks endpoint + retries with OAuth on 401/403 from env token
- `handleResponse` does NOT mark/retry when no env token is active
- `handleResponse` does NOT retry when `RETRY_MARKER_HEADER` is set (prevents loops)
- Fallback gracefully fails when no stored OAuth exists

### Property-based tests: `test/lib/db/env-token-cache.property.test.ts` (new)
- For any `(token, method, path)` triple: mark then check → true
- For any two distinct triples: marks are independent
- TTL invariant: entries with `created_at` older than TTL are always ignored

